properties.name: BS
properties.description: Graduated from Cal Poly with a degree in Biology and coursework in statistics, GIS, and Chemistry. Served as a research associate in Molecular Biology and Applied Biotechnology labs

properties.name: First job
properties.description: After school I landed a gig as a bus driver/tour guide at the SD Zoo. This makes me a great asset in trivia, and also means I can reverse a 40' bus through an S-curve

properties.name: Next job
properties.description: Next, I went to the CA Academy of Sciences where I showed off the living roof, inner workings of the aquarium, and ~46 million specimens. Ask me about the lion eyes

properties.name: Current job
properties.description: Applying mapping and research skills from my biology studies, I started at Cruise as a GIS technician and am now a Data Analyst for the Mapping team. I've also taken a liking to software, so I made this site. Thanks for stopping by!
